Gross Lease Landlord Responsibilities

Under this Gross lease, Landlord is responsible for: building insurance, all utility charges (electric, gas, water), all repairs and maintenance, real estate taxes and assessments, sewer charges, trash/rubbish removal, landscaping, janitorial services, snow removal, and HVAC maintenance (excluding clean room HVAC).
Utility Increase Caveat: If landlord determines utility consumption has increased by 10%+ above prior levels, tenant pays the additional cost as Additional Rent.

Property Assessment

Strengths

  • High-end finishes and construction
  • Walk-up, single story with direct parking access
  • Signage opportunity
  • Light industrial zoningvaluable for today's purchase demand

Weaknesses

  • Low parking ratio
  • Low visibility with limited amenity access
  • Flex/lab component creates disconnect with office users
  • Light industrial zoning does not allow medical use

Opportunities

  • Sublease space is being absorbed
  • Overall availability rate seems to have peaked
  • Interest rates for owner-users have gone down considerably
  • Limited supply of light industrial purchase options
  • Limited supply of quality lab space
  • High electricity capacity potential (nearby micro data centers)

Threats

  • Low competing rental rates ($14.50/SF NNN at Northmeadow Pky)
  • Soft leasing market = extended downtime risk
  • Vacancy 282 bps above 10-yr avg (Roswell), 473 bps above (N Fulton), and most importantly 643 bps above average in the immediate Old Ellis Light Industrial District
  • Office tenant demand misaligned with location
  • High tenant demand for energy and amenities
  • Construction costs at all-time high with lengthy diligence

ACT+ Outbound Strategy Proactive, intelligence-driven buyer generation

Where RREAL sets the tone and attracts active buyers, ACT+ goes further to proactively uncover qualified buyers who would not otherwise be looking.

  • Leverage every employee in our company to extend reach. Our entire team shares new listings across their professional networks, instantly connecting your property to thousands of potential buyers and referral sources.
  • Campaign begins with a coordinated LinkedIn launch. We kick off every listing with a strategic social media push, tagging team members and industry contacts to maximize visibility during the critical first week.
  • Visibility expands rapidly beyond a single broker's audience. A solo broker might have 500 connections. Our team approach multiplies that reach exponentially, ensuring your property is seen by the right people across the region.
Why it matters: Momentum builds faster when opportunities are shared through trusted professional networks.
  • The most serious buyers are typically represented by brokers. Owner-users and investors often rely on tenant rep or buyer's brokers to source opportunities. Reaching those brokers first means reaching the most qualified buyers first.
  • We maintain a curated list of top brokers for this asset type and submarket. This isn't a mass email blast to a generic database. We've identified the specific brokers who are actively working deals in North Fulton, and we reach out to them directly.
  • Custom broker e-blasts ensure immediate awareness. Our targeted communications put your property in front of brokers who already have active buyer requirementsbefore they even see it on CoStar or LoopNet.
Why it matters: Early broker awareness drives early traction.
  • Analyze the building, zoning, and use flexibility to define ideal buyer profiles. We study what types of businesses fit this spaceconsidering layout, parking, signage, and zoningthen build a targeted list of companies that match.
  • Use advanced data tools to identify relevant companies and decision-makers. We leverage business intelligence platforms to find growing companies in the right industries, at the right size, in the right geographythen identify the specific people who make real estate decisions.
  • Deploy proprietary AI outreach technology with data-backed messaging. Our outreach isn't generic spam. We use AI tools to craft personalized, relevant messages that speak directly to each prospect's situation and needs.
  • Outreach is intentional, scalable, and repeatable. This isn't a one-and-done effort. We systematically work through target lists, track responses, and refine our approach based on what's generating engagement.
Why it matters: Precision outreach converts awareness into real conversations.
  • Track new competing sale listings and monitor sale comps in real time. We keep a close eye on what else hits the market and what's trading. If a comparable building sells above or below expectations, we factor that into our strategy immediately.
  • Follow development announcements and pipeline activity. New construction, proposed projects, and zoning changes can all impact buyer perception and pricing. We monitor these developments so you're never caught off guard.
  • Track amenity openings, road improvements, and city planning initiatives. A new restaurant opening nearby, a road widening project, or a rezoning decision can shift the narrative around your property. We stay informed and adjust messaging accordingly.
  • Refine positioning, outreach, and pricing guidance as conditions evolve. The market today isn't the market in six months. We continuously evaluate feedback, showing activity, and market trends to keep your listing optimally positioned throughout the process.
Why it matters: Markets change. Staying ahead of them preserves leverage.

Strategy 1

List For Lease AND For Sale

Why consider a sale? The leasing market has seen a rapid decline over the last 5 years, and demand has shiftedparticularly in the Old Ellis Light Industrial district. Tenants are seeking highly amenitized, high-energy locations. The workplace has become less of a commodity. Meanwhile, owner-user demand for light industrial properties remains strong, and interest rates have improved. Additionally, your equity could be better utilized in another asset that produces more income with less risk.

Execution Roadmap
What's the Plan?

30-Day Marketing Launch Plan

A structured 4-week plan to position the property for maximum exposure and qualified prospects.

Week 1 Foundation & Planning
  • Schedule production company to visit the site
  • Perform site visit for information gathering and staging recommendations prior to filming
  • Collect, clarify, and document all property, systems, and operating information with ownership assistance
  • Meet with marketing director for planning marketing content
  • Plan outbound marketing strategy
  • Use data tools like PlacerAI for a deep dive into demographics and positioning
Week 2 Content Development
  • Finalize minimum viable product for marketing directly to prospects
  • Begin working on full design of marketing flyer
  • Draft email for buyer and broker prospect list
  • Draft email for direct buyer list
  • Deep dive into the comp set to make the case for "Why 1100 Old Ellis?"
  • Schedule meetings with City of Roswell economic development team and Metro Atlanta Chamber to put this listing on their radar for foreign companies seeking a central metro Atlanta location
Week 3 Soft Launch & Outreach
  • Finalize initial emails and send
  • Review initial draft of marketing flyer and make final edits
  • Follow-up with outreach and prospects from initial e-blasts and phone calls
  • Extract contact information for Old Ellis neighbors
  • Coming Soon LinkedIn post
Week 4 GO LIVE!
  • Finalize marketing material
  • Launch listing on all listing sites
  • Broker E-blast
  • CDX mailer
  • Reach out directly to Old Ellis neighbors
  • Analyze results of direct mailer, adjust, expand research, repeat

About Industry Real Estate Partners
Industry Real Estate Partners (IREP) was established in 2021 in Atlanta, Georgia. The founding principals bring more than 50 years of combined real estate experience and $4.5B+ in completed commercial real estate transactions and 30MM+ square feet sold. Our team supports the facilitation of highest and best real estate solutions in key growth markets around the United States.

Our guiding mission is to blend institutional commercial real estate experience with a personalized approach for excellent client service. Through an undeterred work ethic and the diverse backgrounds of our three principals, we operate with the highest level of integrity to create value and promote efficiency.
